// IF-162 minimal repro: dual-channel `assignWaveIndex` with two
// placeholders of DIFFERENT sizes computes the merged length from the
// FIRST placeholder instead of the MAX.  Recon emits a half-size
// waveform section.
//
// Symptom is identical to IF-157 (mergeWaveforms first-signal-length
// bug, fixed for playWave path); this is the assignWaveIndex / pinned
// CT entry path which has the same bug independently.

wave p_small = placeholder(256, true, true);
wave p_large = placeholder(512, true, true);

assignWaveIndex(1, p_small, 2, p_large, 13);
executeTableEntry(13);
